HEADWORD: Creeks
<hw>Creeks</hw> <pr>(kr⟦emac⟧ks)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>;
<sing><it>sing.</it> <singw>Creek</singw></sing>. <fld>(Ethnol.)</fld>
<def>A tribe or confederacy of North American Indians, including the
Muskogees, Seminoles, Uchees, and other subordinate tribes. They
formerly inhabited Georgia, Florida, and Alabama.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

